lence and/or prayer, just silence) do much better in school because people don't realize how much noise dominates our days and inhibits our thought. I don't think 2 minutes of silence could possibly hinder our absolutely terrible public education any further than it's current decrepit state. &#10;It's all good. Don't worry, I agree. Trust me, I know. First hand.&#10;Learn what? The BS they half-arsedly try to teach us? I attended private school up until age 14, and I have yet to learn anything from our public ed. system. &#10;True, but the scenario at the top was obviously over-the-top wrong. I just wanted to present a much more common iteration. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="946" language="en" documentId="1909" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="The 68" date="10th September 2006 11:53 PM" docType="forumpost" origUrl="http://www.volconvo.com/forums/showthread.php?t=11753&amp;page=2" topic="prayer-in-schools" thumbsUp="0" thumbsDown="0" origId="1909" notes="" title="The Bible in Public Schools"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="9"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="43" sofa="1" begin="10" end="596"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="47" sofa="1" begin="597" end="663"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="51" sofa="1" begin="664" end="822"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="55" sofa="1" begin="823" end="946"/><types:PersuasivenessAnnotationMetaData xmi:id="59" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" annotator="annotator1" isPersuasive="true" labelDetailed="P1" isGold="false" comment="&quot;but the purpose is to give students time to collect thoughts, pray,&quot;&#13;&#10;&quot; I don't think 2 minutes of silence could possibly hinder our absolutely terrible public education any further than it's current decrepit state. &quot;" annotationBatchName="batch2-690documents" conflictResolvingAnnotation="false"/><types:PersuasivenessAnnotationMetaData xmi:id="71" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" annotator="annotator3" i